description: Kevin Kelsy scored his first MLS goals, Luciano Acosta added a goal and an assists and FC Cincinnati beat the Columbus Crew 2-1 to extend its win streak to four games.
title: Kevin Kelsey scores first MLS goal to help Cincinnati beat Crew 2-1

description: Rhys Hoskins hit a go-ahead three-run home run in the seventh inning and the Milwaukee Brewers beat St.
title: Rhys Hoskins slugs 3-run homer in 7th to help Brewers send Cardinals to 7th straight loss

description: Patrick Agyemang scored early in the second half and Kristijan Kahlina made three saves to lead Charlotte FC to a 1-0 victory over Nashville SC.
title: Agyemang, Kahlina lead Charlotte to 1-0 victory over Nashville

description: Luis Muriel scored two goals — his first in MLS — and Pedro Gallese stopped a penalty kick in the 88th minute to help Orlando City beat the Philadelphia Union 3-2.
title: Luis Muriel scores first 2 MLS goals, Gallese stops late PK as Orlando City beats Union 3-2

description: Lionel Messi played the entire game despite a first-half injury scare, Benjamin Cremaschi broke a tie in the 59th minute and Inter Miami overcame an early two-goal deficit to beat Montreal 3-2 on Saturday night for its fifth consecutive Major League Soccer win.
title: Messi plays through a scare, Inter Miami rallies past Montreal 3-2 for fifth straight win

description: Lewis Morgan had an early goal and picked up an assist late to lead the New York Red Bulls to a 4-2 victory over the New England Revolution.
title: Morgan sparks Red Bulls to 4-2 victory over Revolution

description: Matt Chapman hit a grand slam in the first inning to lead the struggling San Francisco Giants to a 5-1 victory over the Cincinnati Reds.
title: Matt Chapman's grand slam leads the Giants past the Reds 5-1

description: Brady Skjei scored on the power play with 3:11 left to help the Carolina Hurricanes beat the New York Rangers 4-3, staving off a sweep by winning Game 4 of the second-round playoff series.
title: Skjei ends Carolina's power-play woes, helps Hurricanes beat Rangers 4-3 to extend 2nd-round series

description: Paul Skenes struck out seven over four-plus innings in his major league debut and Yasmani Grandal hit a go-ahead three-run homer as the Pittsburgh Pirates edged the Chicago Cubs 10-9.
title: Skenes strikes out 7 in debut, Pirates hit 5 homers in 10-9 victory over the Cubs

description: Christian Benteke scored three goals — his second hat trick this season — and Jared Stroud had two assists to help D.C. United beat Atlanta United 3-2.
title: Benteke scores 3 goals to help DC United beat Atlanta United 3-2

description: Mike Clevinger combined with three relievers on a four-hitter, and the Chicago White Sox topped the Cleveland Guardians 3-1 for their season-high fourth consecutive victory.
title: Clevinger combines with 3 relievers on a 4-hitter as the White Sox beat the Guardians 3-1

description: The Chicago Cubs drew six bases-loaded walks in the fifth inning against the Pittsburgh Pirates on Saturday, the most by a major league team in a single inning in 65 years.
title: Cubs draw 6 bases-loaded walks in 5th vs. Pirates, most in 1 inning in 65 years

description: The first recipient of a genetically modified pig kidney transplant has died nearly two months after he underwent the procedure.
title: First person to receive a genetically modified pig kidney transplant dies nearly 2 months later

description: Mark Canha hit a grand slam in a seven-run second inning, Kerry Carpenter homered twice and Detroit beat Houston 8-2 on Saturday night.
title: Mark Canha hits grand slam, Kerry Carpenter homers twice in Tigers' 8-2 victory over Astros

description: Lionel Messi and Inter Miami had an injury scare Saturday night. Messi, the eight-time Ballon d’Or winner as the world’s best player, briefly left Inter Miami’s match at Montreal late in the first half after evidently having some sort of issue with his left knee.
title: Messi shaken up during Miami-Montreal match, returns after brief absence

description: Doug Barron shot a 6-under 66 for a share of the Regions Tradition lead with Ernie Els on Saturday, heading into the final round of the PGA Tour Champions’ first major of the season.
title: Els, Barron tied for Regions Tradition lead at 13-under heading into final round

description: The Los Angeles Chargers signed outside linebacker Bud Dupree to bolster an already formidable pass rush.
title: Chargers sign outside linebacker Bud Dupree to help bolster their pass rush

description: Bo Nix was the sixth quarterback selected in last month's NFL draft but the first to sign his rookie contract.
title: Bo Nix gives Sean Payton fresh fodder for praise with array of impressive passes at Broncos minicamp

description: Cavaliers forward Dean Wade is expected to make his playoff debut in Game 3 against the Boston Celtics on Saturday night after being sidelined the past two months with a strained right knee.
title: Cavaliers get back forward Dean Wade against Celtics. Center Jarrett Allen still out with rib injury
